Macro Tip: Bulk Assign Cell Notes from One Row to Another

Use this macro when row 3 contains explanatory text and row 2 contains headers or labels where you want those explanations stored as legacy cell notes.

What you get:
- Notes are applied across all populated columns in row 2.
- Note text is sourced from row 3 in the same column.
- A fast way to document many columns at once without opening each note manually.

Why you would use this:
- Add consistent, hover-based documentation for wide tables.
- Speed up migration of inline helper text into notes.
- Improve workbook usability for collaborators reviewing column definitions.

Sub AddNotesFromRow3ToRow2()
    Dim ws As Worksheet
    Set ws = ActiveSheet
    Dim lastCol As Long
    lastCol = ws.Cells(2, ws.Columns.Count).End(xlToLeft).Column

    Dim i As Long
    For i = 1 To lastCol
        ws.Cells(2, i).NoteText Text:=ws.Cells(3, i).Value
    Next i
End Sub
